<%- include('partials/header') %>
<div class="landing-page">
  <section class="hero hero-split hero-premium">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <p class="eyebrow">Private bet tracking for serious bettors</p>
      <h1>Build a betting record you can actually use.</h1>
      <p class="hero-lead">Bankroll IQ keeps your wagers, bankroll movement, and ROI in one place, so you can stop rebuilding spreadsheets, see whether your edge is holding up, and stake from history, not memory.</p>

      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn" href="/auth/register">Create Free Account</a>
        <a class="btn btn-soft" href="#features">See What You Can Track</a>
      </div>
      <p class="hero-action-note">No spreadsheet cleanup. No manual ROI math. No guessing what moved your bankroll.</p>

      <div class="hero-proof-row" aria-label="What users can review inside Bankroll IQ">
        <div class="proof-pill">
          <strong>Log bets cleanly</strong>
          <span>Save the wager while the details are fresh.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-pill">
          <strong>Track bankroll movement</strong>
          <span>See deposits, withdrawals, and results in the same record.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="proof-pill">
          <strong>Find real leaks</strong>
          <span>Break results down by sport, book, market, and stretch.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-support-grid" aria-label="What Bankroll IQ helps you review">
        <div class="hero-support-card hero-support-card-story">
          <span class="section-label">Why it is different</span>
          <strong>Built to review your process, not chase someone else's picks.</strong>
          <p>Most betting tools feel like either a spreadsheet or a feed. Bankroll IQ gives you a private record you can audit after bets settle, when the real question is whether your process is holding up.</p>
          <ul class="feature-list checked-list hero-inline-list">
            <li>Bet history, notes, and grading stay tied together</li>
            <li>Bankroll movement sits beside betting performance</li>
            <li>CSV import and export keep you out of locked-in tools</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-support-card hero-support-list hero-support-card-spotlight">
          <span class="section-label">What you can see fast</span>
          <div class="hero-support-item">
            <strong>Bankroll trend</strong>
            <span>See whether the curve is actually rising or just swinging around.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-support-item">
            <strong>Recent form</strong>
            <span>Review your last stretch before variance rewrites the story.</span>
          </div>
          <div class="hero-support-item">
            <strong>Category edges</strong>
            <span>Spot which sports, books, and bet types deserve more trust.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

